description: From Middle English anelen, anelien, from Middle English an- (“on”) + Middle English elen (“to anoint”), from Old English ēle (“oil”). Compare English anoil.

verbs.description: anele (third-person singular simple present aneles, present participle aneling, simple past and past participle aneled)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To anoint; to give extreme unction with oil.
